<div id="about-the-community" class="section-spacer">
    <h2 class="sect-title">About Pineridge</h2>
    <div class="col-grid-2">
        <div>
            <p class="par-lg">Developed along with the four ‘Properties’ neighborhoods including the <a href="/rundle.php">Rundle</a>, <a href="/temple.php">Temple</a>, and <a href="/whitehorn.php">Whitehorn</a> in 1974, the community in Pineridge is desirable for young couples, growing families as well the elderly. </p>
            <p class="par-lg">Belonging to the group of four neighborhoods termed as the ‘Properties’, Pineridge is surrounded by 68 Street NE on the east, the Trans Canada Highway on the south, 52 Street NE on the west and the 32 Ave NE on the north.</p>
